From Babb Subject Re Electric power line balls In article Scott Townsend wrote I got a question from my dad which I really can't answer and I'd appreciate some His question is about some diameter balls which are attached to electric power lines in his He's seen up to a half dozen between two Neither of us have any experience with electric power My only guess was that they may be a capacitive device to equalize the inductance of the grid but why so many between two poles I'll bet there's a runway Jeff Babb Programmer SDSU LARC